---
import HelpLayout from "../../layouts/HelpLayout.astro";
---

<HelpLayout title="Creating Your Account" category="Getting Started" description="How to sign up, log in, and manage your Plantgotchi profile.">
  <p>
    Your Plantgotchi account lets you sync plant data across devices and access your garden from
    the web dashboard. Here's how to get set up.
  </p>

  <h2>Signing Up</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Go to <a href="/signup">plantgotchi.com/signup</a> or tap "Sign Up" in the mobile app.</li>
    <li>Enter your email address and choose a password.</li>
    <li>Tap "Create Account" — you're in!</li>
  </ol>
  <p>
    Plantgotchi uses email and password authentication powered by the better-auth library.
    Your credentials are encrypted and session cookies expire after 5 minutes of inactivity,
    then auto-refresh when you interact with the app.
  </p>

  <h2>Logging In</h2>
  <p>
    Visit <a href="/login">plantgotchi.com/login</a> or open the app and tap "Login."
    Enter your email and password, and you'll be taken to your garden dashboard.
  </p>

  <h2>Your Garden Dashboard</h2>
  <p>
    Once logged in, the <a href="/garden">Garden</a> page shows all your plants with their
    current HP, status, and latest sensor readings. From here you can:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Add new plants with the "+" button</li>
    <li>Tap any plant card to see detailed readings and care history</li>
    <li>Log care actions (watering, fertilizing, pruning, etc.)</li>
    <li>View AI and rule-based recommendations</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Account Security</h2>
  <p>
    Choose a strong password (12+ characters recommended). Your session data and plant records
    are stored in a Turso cloud database, with all communication encrypted over HTTPS.
    User IDs are linked to your plants, care logs, and recommendations so your data stays private.
  </p>
</HelpLayout>
